Sentencas: The effect of contact area between electrode and current collector (i.e., the interconnect) on the performance of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) has been investigated using current collector with various contact area on the (Pr,Sr)MnO3 (PSM) cathode side.
Titulo: Effect of contact between electrode and current collector on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When the contact area of the current collector increased from 4.6% to 27.2%, the cell resistance decreased from 1.43 to 0.19 Omega cm(2) at 800degreesC, a reduction of more than 80%.
Titulo: Effect of contact between electrode and current collector on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the polarization losses of the cell were also significantly reduced with the increase in the contact area of the current collector.
Titulo: Effect of contact between electrode and current collector on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that there is close correlation between the contact area of the current collector and the cell performance.
Titulo: Effect of contact between electrode and current collector on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This shows that the constriction effect as frequently observed in solid electrolyte cells not only occurs at the electrode/electrolyte interface but also at the interface of the electrode/current collector.

Sentencas: A hypothesis on the effect of the discrete contact between current collector and electrode on the current distribution in the electrolyte cell has been proposed.
